### Finite Horizon Markov Decision Process

We also consider the following finite horizon Markov decision process (MDP), denoted by \(\mathcal{M}:=(H,\mathcal{S}_{1:H},\mathcal{A}_{1:H},\mathbb{P}_{2:H},\sigma, \bm{\rho}_{1})\). \(H\in\mathbb{Z}_{+}\) denotes the number of horizon; \(\mathcal{S}_{1:H}=(\mathcal{S}_{1},\cdots,\mathcal{S}_{H})\) is a sequence of \(H\) finite state spaces; \(\mathcal{A}_{1:H}=(\mathcal{A}_{1},\cdots,\mathcal{A}_{H})\) is a sequence of \(H\) finite action spaces; \(\mathbb{P}_{h}(s_{h}|s_{h-1},a_{h-1})\) denotes the probability of transitioning from \(s_{h-1}\) to \(s_{h}\) under playing action \(a_{h-1}\) at horizon \(h-1\); \(\sigma:\mathcal{S}_{1:H}\times\mathcal{A}_{1:H}\rightarrow[0,1]\)is a cost function; \(\bm{\rho}_{1}\) is a initial state distribution over \(S_{1}\).

\(\bm{\pi}=(\bm{\pi}_{1},\cdots,\bm{\pi}_{H}):\mathcal{S}_{1:H}\rightarrow\Delta_ {\mathcal{A}_{1}}\times\cdots\times\Delta_{\mathcal{A}_{H}}\) denotes a stochastic policy. Similarly, we use \(\mathbf{Pr}_{h}^{\bm{\pi}_{1:h-1}}(s^{\prime}|s)=\mathbf{Pr}_{h}^{\bm{\pi}_{1:h -1}}(s_{h}=s^{\prime}|s_{1}=s)\) to denote the probability of visiting the state \(s^{\prime}\) from the state \(s\) at horizon \(h\) according to policy \(\bm{\pi}_{1:h-1}\). Let trajectory \(\tau=(s_{h},a_{h})_{h=1}^{H}\), where \(s_{1}\sim\bm{\rho}_{1}\), and, for all subsequent horizon \(h\), \(a_{h}\sim\bm{\pi}_{h}(\cdot|s_{h})\) and \(s_{h+1}\sim\mathbb{P}_{h+1}(\cdot|s_{h},a_{h})\). The value function \(V_{h}^{\bm{\pi}_{h,H}}:\mathcal{S}_{h}\rightarrow\mathbb{R}\) is defined as the sum of future cost starting at state \(s_{h}\) and executing\(\bm{\pi}_{h:H}=(\bm{\pi}_{h},\cdots,\bm{\pi}_{H})\), i.e.,

\[V_{h}^{\bm{\pi}_{h:H}}(s_{h})=\mathbb{E}\left[\left.\sum_{h^{\prime}=h}^{H} \sigma(s_{h^{\prime}},a_{h^{\prime}})\right|\bm{\pi}_{h:H},s_{h}\right].\]

For convenience, we define \(V_{1}^{\bm{\pi}}(s_{1})=V_{1}^{\bm{\pi}_{1:H}}(s_{1})\). Moreover, we define the action-value function \(Q_{h}^{\bm{\pi}_{h+1:H}}:\mathcal{S}_{h}\times\mathcal{A}_{h}\to[0,1+H-h]\) as follows:

\[Q_{h}^{\bm{\pi}_{h+1:H}}(s_{h},a_{h})=\sigma(s_{h},a_{h})+\mathbb{E}\left[ \left.\sum_{h^{\prime}=h+1}^{H}\sigma(s_{h^{\prime}},a_{h^{\prime}})\right| \bm{\pi}_{h+1:H},s_{h},a_{h}\right].\]

